Persian Gulf Stocks: Global Investment House, Oman’s Renaissance

-- B y   Z a h r a   H a n k i r
-- 
2011-08-16T11:18:51Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-16/persian-gulf-stocks-qatar-meat-livestock-oman-s-renaissance.html
Dubai’s  DFM General Index (DFMGI)  dropped
0.3 percent at the 2 p.m. close in the emirate. Abu Dhabi’s  ADX
General Index (ADSMI)  declined 0.6 percent, while Qatar’s  QE Index (DSM)  rose
0.3 percent.  The following shares were active in the Persian Gulf
region. Stock symbols are in parenthesis.  Global Investment House KSCC (GLOBAL)   rallied the most
on record, surging 14 percent to 21 fils. Kuwait’s biggest
investment bank said second-quarter loss narrowed as interest
expenses and operating costs declined. The loss was 16.7 million
dinars ($61 million) compared with a loss of 20.3 million dinars
a year earlier.  Renaissance Services SAOG (RNSS)   slumped to the lowest
since April 2009, losing 10 percent to 0.559 rial. The Omani
provider of services to the oil and gas industry was cut to
“neutral” from “buy” with a 12-month price estimate of 0.68
rial at EFG-Hermes Holding SAE.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Zahra Hankir in Dubai at 
 zhankir@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
